Ad Text:
12+12+12 month contract
NV1 security clearance required
Experience in financial crime, regulation or intelligence environments is highly desirable

Our client, a large Australian Federal Government financial intelligence agency, require the services of three experienced Senior Change Managers.

Duties of the Senior Change Manager

Develop, manage, communicate and implement end-to end change management plans to maximise adoption, onboarding and build awareness of Program benefits and deliverables;
Work with key stakeholders (including executive leaders, business managers, product owners and customers) to facilitate the analysis and review of impacts and business readiness, assisting with the development of change initiatives and associated communications;
Track implementation of change management activities, providing input into stakeholder reporting, identifying risks and issues and developing appropriate mitigations;
Provide reporting and other artefacts to project teams and governance committees on status of change management & communication initiatives.

Skills / Experience required

Demonstrated experience working in Agile projects and within a digital context;
Demonstrated knowledge and understanding of change management principles, methodologies and tools;
Demonstrated ability to develop change management strategies/plans including assessing impacts, communications/awareness, training and adoption plans, and embed lessons learned;
Demonstrated experience within behavioural, process and organisational change;
Change certification (Prosci or equivalent) is required;
Demonstrated experience liaising with a wide range of stakeholders, including reporting entities, partner agencies and other government agencies.

How to apply

To be considered for this role, please forward your resume to Coral by clicking the Quick Apply button. Please note that this role closes on Wednesday, 18 March 2026 @ 10am. 

JOB ID: CW666760 / LH-05835

Recruitment Hive: (02) 6299 1006

We Value Diversity

The Recruitment Hive is a proud Equal Opportunity Employer. We recognise the value of diverse perspectives and experience and are committed to an inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued and respected for who they are. We encourage people with disability, indigenous, veterans and people of all backgrounds and abilities to express their interest in this role.

The Company 

Our client is an instantly recognisable, global business that most people have some form of connection to. 

The Role 

We are looking for a strong Business Analyst with proven experience with Dynamics AX – FinOps to join our clients team in Western Sydney.  

Key Responsibilities 

Lead end‑to‑end requirements activities for large programs (ERP- D365 F&O, Salesforce, LOS/LMS), including analysis, validation, and requirements traceability;
Produce high‑quality artefacts: BRDs, FRDs, user stories with acceptance criteria, process maps (BPMN), data mappings/models, use cases, and RTMs;
Translate business requirements into clear, testable specifications that enable accurate technical design, development, and test planning;
Conduct gap analysis and impact assessment for changes;
Facilitate workshops, interviews, and discovery sessions with cross‑functional stakeholders (Collections, Customer Service, Credit, Risk, Finance, Insurance, Compliance, Product, Sales);
Support solution assessment & design, document current/target state processes, identify gaps, non‑functional requirements, and data implications;
Define and lead QA/UAT - test planning, test case review, defect triage, and business sign‑off;
Work closely with the Project Manager to shape scope, manage change, and control delivery risks and dependencies across streams;
Maintain the requirements backlog, ensure prioritisation aligns with business value and capacity, and support sprints where Agile;
Contribute to vendor SOWs, estimates, and deliverable acceptance criteria;
Track benefits realisation metrics and ensure traceability from requirements to outcomes; 
Orchestrate intake, triage, business case development, budget tracking and prioritisation via the Change Council; maintain change calendars and resolve conflicts;
Establish and maintain requirements/change standards, templates, and quality and security gates;
Drive process simplification and automation opportunities within the portfolio;
Reporting to ensure business value delivery;
ERP Replacement: Collaborate on finance process design (O2C, P2P, R2R), master data governance, mapping, integrations, and cutover planning;
Salesforce Initiatives: Capture Sales/Service/Experience Cloud requirements, lead data and integration requirements (e.g., to core platforms and finance), and ensure field‑level security alignment; 
Loan Origination & Management Systems: Support RFP, Document credit decisioning, underwriting, pricing, KYC/AML, servicing, collections, and regulatory reporting requirements;
Support integration and data requirements (APIs, eventing, batch), data lineage, and data quality rules;
Capture non‑functional requirements (security, privacy, performance, scalability, resiliency, observability); and 
Ensure alignment to enterprise data standards, access controls, and PII handling. 
About you 

5 - 8+ years Business Analysis experience within financial services (banking, consumer/asset finance, fintech, or similar regulated environments);
Demonstrated delivery on replacement or major uplift projects;
Proven experience collaborating with outsourced/offshore technology teams (preferably India) on bespoke systems;
Exposure to US financial services environments and cyber/security expectations (e.g., NIST CSF, SOC 2, GLBA/FFIEC), with practical application to BA deliverables;
Proficiency with Jira/Confluence or Azure DevOps, Visio/Lucidchart, process modelling (BPMN), and requirements traceability;
Strong data analysis basics (SQL for querying/validation preferred), and experience with API/integration requirements;
Tertiary qualifications in Business, Information Systems, Finance or related; IIBA CBAP/CCBA or Agile BA certification advantageous;
Experience working on ERP implementations, business process improvements and translation;
Outstanding requirements engineering and documentation quality;
Stakeholder facilitation and clear communication across business, technology, and vendors; 
Analytical problem solving with a bias to measurable outcomes and value;
Risk awareness: build security, privacy, and compliance into requirements; 
Delivery discipline: scope control, change control, and benefits traceability; 
Influence & collaboration across time zones and cultures (incl. India team); and 
Adaptability across Waterfall, Agile, and hybrid delivery frameworks. 
